commit.message:
config.gcc: Include dbxelf.h before elfos.h.

2001-12-06  David O'Brien  <obrien@FreeBSD.org>
	* config.gcc: Include dbxelf.h before elfos.h.
	* elfos.h: Don't include dbxelf.h, let config.gcc handle it.

Approved by:  Richard Henderson <rth@redhat.com>
              Message-ID: <20011205224713.D9059@redhat.com>

From-SVN: r47723

files.patch:
@@ -1,3 +1,8 @@

+
+	* config.gcc: Include dbxelf.h before elfos.h.

+

 #			"$cpu_type/$cpu_type.h". Usually it's constructed
 #			per target in a way like this:
-#			tm_file="${tm_file} elfos.h svr4.h ${cpu_type.h}/elf.h"
+#			tm_file="${tm_file} dbxelf.h elfos.h svr4.h ${cpu_type.h}/elf.h"
 #			Note that the preferred order is:
 #			- specific target header "${cpu_type}/${cpu_type.h}"
-#			- generic headers like elfos.h, netware.h, etc.
+#			- generic headers like dbxelf.h elfos.h, netware.h, etc.
 #			- specializing target headers like ${cpu_type.h}/elf.h
 #			This helps to keep OS specific stuff out of the CPU
 #			defining header ${cpu_type}/${cpu_type.h}.
